observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a) General Services Officer to coordinate with the Municipal Engineer to prepare the road map of the Municipality to facilitate the proper reporting and preparation of inventory of its Road Networks, and maintain the required Local Road Network Property Card;
b) Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
c) Inventory Committee to prepare and submit yearly a separate Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network; and
d) Municipal Accountant to provide a separate disclosure of the Road Networks account in the Notes to Financial Statement using the prescribed format and maintain the required Local Road Network Ledger Card.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
 a) General Services Officer to coordinate with the Municipal Engineer to prepare the road map of the Municipality to facilitate the proper reporting and preparation of inventory of its Road Networks, and maintain the required Local Road Network Property Card;
 b) Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and General Services Officer/Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
 c) Inventory Committee to prepare and submit yearly a separate Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network; and
 d) Municipal Accountant to provide disclosure of the Road Networks account in the Notes to the Financial Statement using the prescribed format and maintain the required Local Road Network Ledger Card.

We reiterated our audit observation and recommendations that the Municipal Mayor direct the GSO to:
• conduct physical count of property and provide property tags on all PPE owned by the Municipality;
However, PPEs were not provided with property tags on all PPE owned by the Municipality; • prepare and submit a properly accomplished RPCPPE; • prepare and maintain property cards for each PPE category to support the balance appearing in the general/controlling account; and • issue AREs were to end-users of PPEs and renew them every three years or whenever there is change in accountability.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer to:
prepare and maintain PPELCs and PCs for each PPE category of the Municipality to support the balance appearing in the general/controlling account;
issue Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment (ARE) to end-users of issued PPEs and renew all AREs every three (3) years or whenever there is change in accountability;
conduct physical count of properties and provide property tag on all property, plant and equipment owned by the Municipality;
prepare and submit the Report of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE); and
reconcile the RPCPPE with the books of accounts of the Municipality.
